120 // Must include this header file to use the Mutation++ library
121 #include "mutation++.h"
122 #include <iostream>
123 
124 using namespace Mutation;
125 using namespace Mutation::Thermodynamics;
126 
127 int main()
128 {
129  // Generate the default options for the air11 mixture
130  MixtureOptions opts("air_5");
131  opts.setStateModel("EquilTP");
132 
133  // Change from default thermodynamic database (RRHO) to NASA 9-coefficient
134  // polynomial database
135  opts.setThermodynamicDatabase("RRHO");
136 
137  // Load the mixture with the new options
138  Mixture mix(opts);
139 
140  // Setup the default composition
141  mix.addComposition("N:0.8, O:0.2", true);
142 
143  // Write a header line for the table
144  std::cout << std::setw(7) << "T[K]";
145  for (int i = 0; i < mix.nSpecies(); ++i)
146  std::cout << std::setw(13) << "X_" + mix.speciesName(i);
147  std::cout << std::setw(13) << "Cp[J/kg-K]";
148  std::cout << std::setw(13) << "H[J/kg]";
149  std::cout << std::setw(13) << "S[J/kg-K]";
150  std::cout << std::endl;
151 
152  // Loop over range of temperatures and compute equilibrium values at 1 atm
153  double P = ONEATM;
154  for (int i = 0; i < 58; ++i) {
155  // Compute the temperature
156  double T = 300.0 + static_cast<double>(i) * 100.0;
157 
158  // Set the mixture state equal to the equilibrium state for the given
159  // temperature and pressure
160  mix.setState(&T, &P);
161 
162  // Temperature
163  std::cout << std::setw(7) << mix.T();
164 
165  // Species mole fractions
166  for (int j = 0; j < mix.nSpecies(); ++j)
167  std::cout << std::setw(13) << mix.X()[j];
168 
169  // Other properties
170  std::cout << std::setw(13) << mix.mixtureFrozenCpMass(); // Cp [J/kg-K]
171  std::cout << std::setw(13) << mix.mixtureHMass(); // H [J/kg]
172  std::cout << std::setw(13) << mix.mixtureSMass(); // S [J/kg-K]
173 
174  std::cout << std::endl;
175  }
176 
177  return 0;
178 }
